ARTICLE 10. GENERAL PROVISIONS

10.1. Governing Law and Venue. This Instrument shall be governed by and
construed in accordance with the domestic laws of the jurisdiction wherein the
Licensor maintains its principal place of business or, in the event the
Licensor is an individual, the jurisdiction of their primary residence, without
regard to its conflict of law provisions. The parties hereby unequivocally
consent to the exclusive personal jurisdiction and venue of the competent
courts located within said jurisdiction for any and all legal actions,
disputes, or controversies arising out of or relating to this Instrument.

10.2. Integration and Modification. This Instrument constitutes the entire
agreement concerning the subject matter hereof and supersedes all prior
agreements and representations between the parties. No modification of this
Instrument shall be binding unless in writing and signed by an authorized
representative of the Licensor (or Licensors, if applicable).

10.3. Non-Waiver. No waiver of any term of this Instrument shall be deemed a
further or continuing waiver of such term or any other term, and the failure of
the Licensor to assert any right or provision under this Instrument shall not
constitute a waiver of such right or provision.

10.4. Severability. If any provision of this Instrument is held to be
unenforceable or invalid by a court of competent jurisdiction, such provision
shall be reformed only to the extent necessary to make it enforceable. The
remaining provisions of this Instrument shall remain in full force and effect.

10.5. Assignment. The Licensee may not assign or transfer this Instrument or
any rights granted hereunder without the prior written consent of the Licensor.
The Licensor may assign this Instrument at any time without notice.

10.6. Force Majeure. Neither party shall be liable for any failure or delay in
performance under this Instrument (other than for delay in the payment of money
due and payable hereunder) to the extent said failures or delays are
proximately caused by causes beyond that party's reasonable control and
occurring without its fault or negligence.

10.7. Headings. The headings contained in this Instrument are inserted for
convenience of reference only and shall not affect the construction or
interpretation of this Instrument.

10.8. Third Party Beneficiaries. Nothing in this Instrument is intended to
create any third-party beneficiaries, and no person or entity other than the
Licensor and the Licensee shall have any rights or remedies under this
Instrument.

END OF TERMS AND CONDITIONS
